      <div class="observation" data-observation-id="217">
        <a name="ice-conditions-observation-217"></a>
        <h4>Misty Walsh</h4>
        <h5>Tok</h5>
        <h6>November 7</h6>
        <div class="observation__description">
          <q>Thin ice on river. Can't travel the river yet and there is not enough snow to go overland on snowmachines&mdash;have to use 4&times;4s for setting trapline. Rivers that are not frozen this time of year are a hazard to traveling.</q>

          <p>This change affects trapping. I first started noticing this change in 2005 and now observe it seasonally. It has a strong effect on safety.</p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step" data-step="1">
      <div class="observation" data-observation-id="247">
        <a name="ice-conditions-observation-247"></a>
        <h4>Ronnie Demientieff</h4>
        <h5>Holy Cross</h5>
        <h6>January 1</h6>
        <div class="observation__description">
          <q>Open water in January. Froze to the bottom, then flooded over because of lack of snow (no insulation). This can be dangerous and hard for snow machine travel. It's hard on machines and I had to find a route around.</q>

          <p>This change affects trapping. I first started noticing this change in 2011, but do not observe it seasonally. It has a strong effect on safety.</p>

        </div>
      </div>
